[{"id":"VH979704","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents an experiment showing charged particles trapped in a uniform magnetic field B. A particle source shoots the particles to the right with velocity v toward field B. The magnetic field B points out of the page, and has horizontal range x. The particle moves in a counterclockwise circular path with speed v inside the field.\" height=\"334\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH979704.g02.png\" width=\"400\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Scientists set up an experiment as shown above. Charged particles of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"q\"><math alttext=\"q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> are emitted from a source and initially move with a constant velocity, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v\"><math alttext=\"v\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. The scientists wish to temporarily confine the particles in a uniform magnetic field, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. The region of the magnetic field has a horizontal range <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. To confine the particles, the scientists switch on the magnetic field at the moment when the particles reach the center of its horizontal range. Which of the following is a correct prediction of the results of the experiment?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH979704_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">If the scientists set <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B is greater than, the fraction with numerator 2 m v, and denominator q x\"><math alttext=\"B is greater than, the fraction with numerator 2 m v, and denominator q x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mi>B</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>q</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> , then the particle will be confined to the field.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">If the scientists set <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B is greater than, the fraction with numerator 2 m v, and denominator q x\"><math alttext=\"B is greater than, the fraction with numerator 2 m v, and denominator q x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>q</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> , then the particle will not be confined to the field.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">If the scientists set <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B is greater than, the fraction with numerator m v, and denominator q x\"><math alttext=\"B is greater than, the fraction with numerator m v, and denominator q x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>q</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> , then the particle will be confined to the field.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">If the scientists set <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B is less than, the fraction with numerator m v, and denominator 2 q x\"><math alttext=\"B is less than, the fraction with numerator m v, and denominator 2 q x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> , then the particle will be confined to the field.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">If the scientists set <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B equals, the fraction with numerator m v, and denominator 2 q x\"><math alttext=\"B equals, the fraction with numerator m v, and denominator 2 q x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> , then the particle will be confined to the field.</p>"],"answer":0}]